Cape Town - The City of Cape Town’s very first Fire and Rescue Service spokesperson, Theo Layne, passed away over the weekend, at the age of 55. Layne, who joined the fire services in 1987 and was stationed at Goodwood Fire Station, was the first media liaison officer of the service. Mayco member for safety and security JP Smith confirmed Layne’s death. He described him as “an exceptional firefighter and a great man”. Layne died on Saturday morning. “He was stationed at various fire stations throughout his career, which spanned over 30 years. He was a station Commander until he was medically boarded in May of 2019 after being diagnosed with a terminal lung condition.  “He was the pioneer in the Quality Assurance section of the Command and Control Centre,” Smith said. Layne joined the Command and Control Centre in 2006 and became a media liaison officer in 2009 until he was medically boarded. Layne leaves behind a wife and two sons. shakirah.thebus@inl.co.za Cape Argus